CommonFields.Title: Analyzing the Interfacial Layer Properties in Polymer Nanocomposites by Broadband Dielectric Spectroscopy
Author: Carroll, Bobby
Cheng, Shiwang
Sokolov, Alexei P.

Viscosity.description: Not less than value in Benzene at 20°

ChooseParameter.Other: Filtration of solution to remove dust and impurities
Solution transfer - 30 mL of parent solution transferred into 100 mL roundbottom flask

Additive.Description: SiO2 suspended in ethanol, amount determined by solution concentration and desired nanoparticle loading

Mixing.Description: Addition of SiO2 nanoparticles, ambient condition
Dissolving precipitate into acetone, ambient condition

ChooseParameter.Other: Pseudo-decanting. After 3 hours, solution with polymers attached to nanoparticles is separating to the bottom of the flask. Remove top solution with pipette to remove free polymers. Repeat 7-9 as needed to remove free polymers (was performed 5 times in experiment)

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: NC-80 with Alpha-A impedance analyzer and Quatro Cryosystem temperature controller, frequency: Range from 10^7 to 10^-2 Hz, cooling rate: 10 °C (per interval) from 393-173 K, heating rate: 10 °C (per interval) from 173-393 K.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: TA TGA,  Heating from 313-1073 K at 20 K/min.
